---
fink/blocks -- block-syntax definitions.

Importing this module is what tells the parser to treat `ƒink:` and
`ƒtok:` as block forms (it keys block-mode registration off this import
URL). The blocks themselves are SYNTACTIC: a `ƒink:` block lowers to a
string literal of its verbatim source text at compile time, so the
imported names are never called at runtime.

The bindings below exist only so `{ƒink, ƒtok} = import 'fink/blocks.fnk'`
resolves. They become real quote / source-as-data constructors when
code-as-data lands.
---

ƒink = fn src: src
ƒtok = fn src: src
